  "prompt": "Why Arnab Goswami resign times now? And start entrepreneurs.?",
  "response": "Arnab Goswami resigned from Times Now in November 2016. While he didn't publicly state all the reasons behind his decision, several factors are widely believed to have contributed to it:\n\n*   **Differences in Editorial Vision:** There were reports of disagreements between Goswami and the Times Group management regarding the direction and style of news coverage. Goswami was known for his aggressive and opinionated style, which may have clashed with the more traditional approach of the Times Group.\n\n*   **Desire for Greater Control:** As the editor-in-chief of Times Now, Goswami already had a significant degree of influence. However, he may have felt that starting his own venture would give him complete control over the editorial and business aspects of the news channel.\n\n*   **Entrepreneurial Ambition:** Goswami had a clear vision for a new kind of news channel that he believed would resonate with Indian audiences. Starting Republic TV allowed him to bring that vision to life without the constraints of an established media organization.\n\n*   **Financial Incentives:** Launching a new media venture can be financially rewarding, especially if it is successful. Goswami likely saw the potential to build a valuable company and generate significant wealth.\n\nUltimately, Goswami's decision to resign from Times Now and start Republic TV was likely a combination of these factors. He wanted greater control, a platform to pursue his vision, and the opportunity to build his own business.",
